# Conclusion

While MPPT remains the industry benchmark, its efficiency claims of 95–98% are typically achievable only under laboratory converter conditions.

In real-world operation, overall system efficiency commonly falls into the **70–85%** range.

By contrast, Reflex delivers higher real-world performance through simplicity and directness.

It eliminates:

* DC-DC converters
* PWM modulation
* firmware

Replacing them with comparator threshold logic.

Reflex consistently demonstrates:

* Higher charging efficiency (up to 98% vs MPPT 74%)
* Faster charging times
* Superior irradiance correlation
* Reduced complexity
* Zero firmware overhead

For solar applications where reliability, simplicity, and real-world efficiency matter most, Reflex represents a next-generation alternative to MPPT.

Its architecture reduces cost, complexity, and aligns more naturally with available energy flow.

